{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775884442439,"sessionID":"ses_2850a4f5fffedAJsYmDXiRtqck","part":{"id":"prt_d7af61753001iXxIUXMet5roFL","messageID":"msg_d7af60042001O7AZZmcBKBnhMi","sessionID":"ses_2850a4f5fffedAJsYmDXiRtqck","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_38189f72dbb44d7d92b3fecc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n2: \n3: **AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试**\n4: \n5: ## 1. Architecture Overview\n6: \n7: The AgentCube Python SDK provides a client library for interacting with AgentCube's Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime services. The SDK follows a layered architecture:\n8: \n9: - **Public API Layer** (`agentcube/__init__.py`): Exposes `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient`\n10: - **High-Level Clients** (`code_interpreter.py`, `agent_runtime.py`): User-facing clients with business logic\n11: - **Low-Level Clients** (`clients/`): HTTP communication with control plane and data plane\n12: - **Utilities** (`utils/`): HTTP session management, logging, file I/O helpers\n13: \n14: ## 2. Package Layout\n15: \n16: ```\n17: agentcube/\n18: ├── __init__.py                    # Public exports (CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient)\n19: ├── code_interpreter.py            # CodeInterpreterClient\n20: ├── agent_runtime.py               # AgentRuntimeClient\n21: ├── exceptions.py                  # Exception hierarchy\n22: ├── clients/\n23: │   ├── __init__.py                # Re-exports data plane clients\n24: │   ├── control_plane.py          # ControlPlaneClient (Workload Manager)\n25: │   ├── code_interpreter_data_plane.py  # CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\n26: │   └── agent_runtime_data_plane.py     # AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\n27: └── utils/\n28:     ├── __init__.py\n29:     ├── http.py                    # create_session\n30:     ├── utils.py                   # read_token_from_file\n31:     └── log.py                     # get_logger\n32: \n33: tests/\n34: ├── test_code_interpreter.py       # Tests for CodeInterpreterClient\n35: ├── test_agent_runtime_client.py   # Tests for AgentRuntimeClient\n36: ├── test_control_plane.py          # Tests for ControlPlaneClient\n37: ├── test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py\n38: ├── test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py\n39: ├── test_http.py\n40: ├── test_utils.py\n41: └── test_exceptions.py\n42: ```\n43: \n44: ## 3. Public API Surface\n45: \n46: ### 3.1 Root Exports (`agentcube/__init__.py`)\n47: \n48: ```python\n49: from .code_interpreter import CodeInterpreterClient\n50: from .agent_runtime import AgentRuntimeClient\n51: \n52: __all__ = [\"CodeInterpreterClient\", \"AgentRuntimeClient\"]\n53: ```\n54: \n55: ### 3.2 Client Exports (`agentcube/clients/__init__.py`)\n56: \n57: ```python\n58: __all__ = [\n59:     \"ControlPlaneClient\",\n60:     \"CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient\",\n61:     \"AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient\",\n62: ]\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ## 4. Client Classes\n66: \n67: ### 4.1 CodeInterpreterClient (`agentcube/code_interpreter.py`)\n68: \n69: **Purpose**: High-level client for Code Interpreter sessions.\n70: \n71: **Constructor Parameters**:\n72: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n73: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n74: | `name` | `str` | `\"my-interpreter\"` | Session name |\n75: | `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n76: | `ttl` | `int` | `3600` | Session TTL in seconds |\n77: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Control plane URL |\n78: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Data plane router URL (required) |\n79: | `auth_token` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Auth token for control plane |\n80: | `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable debug logging |\n81: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Reuse existing session |\n82: \n83: **Instance Attributes**:\n84: - `name`, `namespace`, `ttl`, `verbose`: Configuration values\n85: - `logger`: Logger instance\n86: - `cp_client`: ControlPlaneClient instance\n87: - `router_url`: Router URL string\n88: - `session_id`: Current session ID\n89: - `dp_client`: CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient instance\n90: \n91: **Methods**:\n92: | Method | Description |\n93: |--------|-------------|\n94: | `__enter__`/`__exit__` | Context manager protocol |\n95: | `stop()` | Cleanup session and close clients |\n96: | `execute_command(command, timeout)` | Execute shell command |\n97: | `run_code(language, code, timeout)` | Run code in specified language |\n98: | `write_file(content, remote_path)` | Write file to remote session |\n99: | `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` | Upload local file |\n100: | `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` | Download remote file |\n101: | `list_files(path)` | List files in remote path |\n102: \n103: ### 4.2 AgentRuntimeClient (`agentcube/agent_runtime.py`)\n104: \n105: **Purpose**: High-level client for Agent Runtime invocations.\n106: \n107: **Constructor Parameters**:\n108: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n109: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n110: | `agent_name` | `str` | `\"my-agent\"` | Agent name |\n111: | `namespace` | `str` | `\"default\"` | Kubernetes namespace |\n112: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Data plane router URL (required) |\n113: | `verbose` | `bool` | `False` | Enable debug logging |\n114: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Reuse existing session |\n115: | `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Request timeout |\n116: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connection timeout |\n117: \n118: **Instance Attributes**:\n119: - `agent_name`, `namespace`, `timeout`, `connect_timeout`: Configuration\n120: - `logger`: Logger instance\n121: - `router_url`: Router URL string\n122: - `session_id`: Current session ID\n123: - `dp_client`: AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient instance\n124: \n125: **Methods**:\n126: | Method | Description |\n127: |--------|-------------|\n128: | `__enter__`/`__exit__` | Context manager protocol |\n129: | `invoke(payload, timeout)` | Invoke agent with payload |\n130: | `close()` | Close client and release resources |\n131: \n132: ### 4.3 ControlPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/control_plane.py`)\n133: \n134: **Purpose**: Low-level client for Workload Manager (control plane) operations.\n135: \n136: **Constructor Parameters**:\n137: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n138: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n139: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Control plane URL (required) |\n140: | `auth_token` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Auth token |\n141: | `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Request timeout |\n142: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connection timeout |\n143: | `pool_connections` | `int` | `10` | HTTP adapter pool connections |\n144: | `pool_maxsize` | `int` | `10` | HTTP adapter pool max size |\n145: \n146: **Methods**:\n147: | Method | Description |\n148: |--------|-------------|\n149: | `create_session(name, namespace, metadata, ttl)` | Create new session, returns sessionId |\n150: | `delete_session(session_id)` | Delete session (404 returns True) |\n151: | `close()` | Close HTTP session |\n152: \n153: ### 4.4 CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py`)\n154: \n155: **Purpose**: Low-level client for Code Interpreter data plane operations.\n156: \n157: **Constructor Parameters**:\n158: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n159: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n160: | `session_id` | `str` | Required | Session identifier |\n161: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL |\n162: | `namespace` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Namespace |\n163: | `cr_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Custom resource name |\n164: | `base_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Explicit base URL |\n165: | `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Request timeout |\n166: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connection timeout |\n167: \n168: **Methods**:\n169: | Method | Description |\n170: |--------|-------------|\n171: | `execute_command(command, timeout)` | Execute shell command |\n172: | `run_code(language, code, timeout)` | Run code |\n173: | `write_file(content, remote_path)` | Write file (base64) |\n174: | `upload_file(local_path, remote_path)` | Upload file (multipart) |\n175: | `download_file(remote_path, local_path)` | Download file (stream) |\n176: | `list_files(path)` | List files |\n177: | `close()` | Close HTTP session |\n178: \n179: ### 4.5 AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient (`agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py`)\n180: \n181: **Purpose**: Low-level client for Agent Runtime data plane operations.\n182: \n183: **Class Constant**:\n184: - `SESSION_HEADER = \"x-agentcube-session-id\"`\n185: \n186: **Constructor Parameters**:\n187: | Parameter | Type | Default | Description |\n188: |-----------|------|---------|-------------|\n189: | `router_url` | `str` | Required | Router URL |\n190: | `namespace` | `str` | Required | Namespace |\n191: | `agent_name` | `str` | Required | Agent name |\n192: | `timeout` | `int` | `120` | Request timeout |\n193: | `connect_timeout` | `float` | `5.0` | Connection timeout |\n194: \n195: **Methods**:\n196: | Method | Description |\n197: |--------|-------------|\n198: | `bootstrap_session_id()` | GET to fetch session ID from header |\n199: | `invoke(session_id, payload, timeout)` | POST JSON payload |\n200: | `close()` | Close HTTP session |\n201: \n202: ## 5. HTTP API Contracts\n203: \n204: ### 5.1 Control Plane (Workload Manager)\n205: \n206: | Method | Path | Body | Response |\n207: |--------|------|------|----------|\n208: | `POST` | `/v1/code-interpreter` | `{\"name\", \"namespace\", \"ttl\", \"metadata\"}` | `{\"sessionId\": \"...\"}` |\n209: | `DELETE` | `/v1/code-interpreter/sessions/{session_id}` | — | 200 or 404 (treated as success) |\n210: \n211: **Headers**:\n212: - `Content-Type: application/json`\n213: - `Authorization: Bearer {token}` (if token provided)\n214: \n215: ### 5.2 Data Plane — Code Interpreter\n216: \n217: **Base URL Construction**:\n218: ```\n219: {router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/code-interpreters/{cr_name}/invocations/\n220: ```\n221: \n222: | Method | Relative Path | Body | Notes |\n223: |--------|---------------|------|-------|\n224: | `POST` | `api/execute` | `{\"command\": [...], \"timeout\": \"<n>s\"}` | Read timeout = timeout + 2s |\n225: | `POST` | `api/files` (JSON) | `{\"path\", \"content\" (base64), \"mode\": \"0644\"}` | |\n226: | `POST` | `api/files` (multipart) | `files={'file': ...}`, `data={'path', 'mode'}` | |\n227: | `GET` | `api/files/{clean_path}` | — | Stream for download |\n228: | `GET` | `api/files?path=...` | — | List files |\n229: \n230: **Headers**:\n231: - Default: `x-agentcube-session-id: {session_id}`\n232: - JSON: `Content-Type: application/json`\n233: \n234: ### 5.3 Data Plane — Agent Runtime\n235: \n236: **Base URL Construction**:\n237: ```\n238: {router_url}/v1/namespaces/{namespace}/agent-runtimes/{agent_name}/invocations/\n239: ```\n240: \n241: | Method | Path | Headers | Body |\n242: |--------|------|---------|------|\n243: | `GET` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id` | — |\n244: | `POST` | `self.base_url` | `x-agentcube-session-id`, `Content-Type: application/json` | JSON payload |\n245: \n246: ## 6. Configuration Resolution\n247: \n248: There is **no** dedicated configuration dataclass. Defaults and environment resolution are distributed:\n249: \n250: | Component | Resolved from |\n251: |-----------|---------------|\n252: | ControlPlaneClient base_url | `workload_manager_url` arg or `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` env |\n253: | ControlPlaneClient auth | `auth_token` arg or `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token` |\n254: | CodeInterpreterClient router_url | `router_url` arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n255: | AgentRuntimeClient router_url | `router_url` arg or `ROUTER_URL` env (required) |\n256: | Default timeouts | `timeout=120`, `connect_timeout=5.0` for all clients |\n257: | Pool settings | `pool_connections=10`, `pool_maxsize=10` |\n258: \n259: ## 7. Exception Hierarchy (`agentcube/exceptions.py`)\n260: \n261: ```python\n262: class AgentCubeError(Exception):\n263:     \"\"\"Base exception for AgentCube SDK\"\"\"\n264: \n265: class CommandExecutionError(AgentCubeError):\n266:     exit_code: int\n267:     stderr: str\n268:     command: Optional[str]\n269: \n270: class SessionError(AgentCubeError):\n271:     \"\"\"Raised when session creation/management fails\"\"\"\n272: \n273: class DataPlaneError(AgentCubeError):\n274:     \"\"\"Raised when Data Plane operations fail\"\"\"\n275: ```\n276: \n277: ## 8. Utility Functions\n278: \n279: ### 8.1 `create_session` (`agentcube/utils/http.py`)\n280: \n281: Creates `requests.Session` with HTTPAdapter for connection pooling.\n282: \n283: ### 8.2 `read_token_from_file` (`agentcube/utils/utils.py`)\n284: \n285: Reads file contents as token string. Returns `None` on `FileNotFoundError`.\n286: \n287: ### 8.3 `get_logger` (`agentcube/utils/log.py`)\n288: \n289: Returns `logging.Logger` with configurable level (INFO default, DEBUG if verbose).\n290: \n291: ## 9. Testing Strategy\n292: \n293: ### 9.1 Test Framework\n294: \n295: - **pytest** with **pytest-mock** for mocking\n296: - **pytest-asyncio** for async tests\n297: - **pytest-cov** for coverage\n298: \n299: ### 9.2 Test Organization\n300: \n301: Tests mirror the source structure:\n302: - `tests/test_code_interpreter.py` — High-level client tests\n303: - `tests/test_agent_runtime_client.py` — High-level client tests\n304: - `tests/test_control_plane.py` — Control plane HTTP tests\n305: - `tests/test_code_interpreter_data_plane.py` — Data plane HTTP tests\n306: - `tests/test_agent_runtime_data_plane.py` — Data plane HTTP tests\n307: - `tests/test_http.py` — HTTP utility tests\n308: - `tests/test_utils.py` — Utility function tests\n309: - `tests/test_exceptions.py` — Exception hierarchy tests\n310: \n311: ### 9.3 Test Patterns\n312: \n313: **Unit Tests**: Mock HTTP responses to test client logic without network calls.\n314: \n315: **Integration Points**:\n316: - Environment variable resolution (ROUTER_URL, WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL)\n317: - Token file reading from Kubernetes service account path\n318: - Context manager lifecycle (enter/exit)\n319: - Session bootstrap via GET request\n320: \n321: **Error Scenarios**:\n322: - Non-zero exit codes → CommandExecutionError\n323: - Missing session headers → ValueError\n324: - Network failures → SessionError/DataPlaneError\n325: - 404 on delete → Returns True (success)\n326: \n327: ### 9.4 Coverage Areas\n328: \n329: | Component | Coverage |\n330: |-----------|----------|\n331: | CodeInterpreterClient | Constructor, context manager, execute_command, run_code, file operations, stop |\n332: | AgentRuntimeClient | Constructor, bootstrap, invoke, close |\n333: | ControlPlaneClient | Create session, delete session (404 handling), auth headers |\n334: | CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient | URL construction, execute, run_code, files API, download, list |\n335: | AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient | Bootstrap, invoke, timeout handling |\n336: | Utils | HTTP session, logger, token reading |\n337: | Exceptions | All exception classes and attributes |\n338: \n339: ## 10. Dependencies\n340: \n341: ```toml\n342: dependencies = [\n343:     \"requests\",\n344:     \"PyJWT>=2.0.0\",\n345:     \"cryptography\",\n346: ]\n347: ```\n348: \n349: Build requirements:\n350: - `setuptools>=61.0`\n351: - `wheel`\n352: - Python >=3.10\n353: \n354: ## 11. Acceptance Criteria Verification\n355: \n356: | Requirement | Verified By |\n357: |-------------|-------------|\n358: | CodeInterpreterClient lifecycle | `test_context_manager`, `test_data_plane_init_failure_cleanup`, `test_stop_closes_clients` |\n359: | AgentRuntimeClient lifecycle | `test_context_manager`, `test_bootstrap_session`, `test_close` |\n360: | HTTP client contracts | `test_create_session_success`, `test_delete_session_not_found`, `test_execute_command`, `test_invoke` |\n361: | Session header management | `test_constructor_session_header`, `test_session_header_constant` |\n362: | Exception hierarchy | `test_command_execution_error_attributes`, `test_session_error_inherits`, `test_data_plane_error_inherits` |\n363: | Timeout behavior | `test_execute_command_with_timeout`, `test_invoke_timeout_tuple` |\n\n(End of file - total 363 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Python SDK — Design\n\n**AR-040 — Python SDK/CLI 测试**\n\n## 1. Architecture Overview\n\nThe AgentCube Python SDK provides a client library for interacting with AgentCube's Code Interpreter and Agent Runtime services. The SDK follows a layered architecture:\n\n- **Public API Layer** (`agentcube/__init__.py`): Exposes `CodeInterpreterClient` and `AgentRuntimeClient`\n- **High-Level Clients** (`code_interpreter.py`, `agent_runtime.py`): User-facing clients with business logic\n- **Low-Level Clients** (`clients/`): HTTP communication with control plane and data plane\n- **Utilities** (`utils/`): HTTP session management, logging, file I/O helpers\n\n## 2. Package Layout\n\n```\nagentcube/\n├── __init__.py                    # Public exports (CodeInterpreterClient, AgentRuntimeClient)\n├── code_interpreter.py            # CodeInterpreterClient\n├── agent_runtime.py               # AgentRuntimeClient","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-MiniMax-M2.5_20260410T163134Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775884442418,"end":1775884442436}}}}
